1X9.F.summary: Cemat A/S engages in the operation, development, and sale of properties in Warsaw. The company is involved in the letting of premises and land; and provision of utilities, including power, water and technical gas, facility services, etc. to its tenants. Its portfolio includes land for office, warehouse and production facilities, and investment development sites. As of December 31, 2020, the company had 116 warehouse tenants and total occupancy level approximately 27,215 sqm. The company was formerly known as Topsil Semiconductor Materials A/S and changed its name to Cemat A/S in July 2016. Cemat A/S was founded in 1959 and is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark.

BLVIS-A.CO.summary: Blue Vision A/S engages in the investment of real estate, equities, mortgage deeds, bonds, and other assets. The company was formerly known as Gudme Raaschou Vision A/S and changed its name to Blue Vision A/S in November 2009. Blue Vision A/S was founded in 2002 and is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.

The firm seeks to make direct and indirect investments based on thorough analyses of the property's location and condition. It primarily focuses to invest in the Greater Copenhagen area. Copenhagen Capital A/S is based in Hellerup, Denmark.

FED.CO.summary: Fast Ejendom Denmark is a real estate investment firm specializing in commercial and residential properties. The firm seeks to invest in Denmark with a focus on the Copenhagen metropolitan area, Aarhus and the Triangle Area. Fast Ejendom Denmark is based in Denmark.

GERHSP.CO.summary: German High Street Properties A/S invests in and rents high-street properties in Germany and in the Nordic countries. The company is based in Charlottenlund, Denmark.

JDAN.CO.summary: Jeudan A/S provides property services in Denmark. The company invests in and operates office, residential, and retail properties. The company also provides a range of property-related consulting and building services, as well as car parking services. Jeudan A/S was founded in 1898 and is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.

PRIMOF.CO.summary: Prime Office A/S operates as a real estate company. It primarily invests in centrally located office buildings in Germany. Prime Office A/S is based in Aarhus, Denmark.

PSNRDC-A.CO.summary: Park Street Nordicom A/S operates as a real estate investment and asset management company. The company owns and manages portfolio of commercial properties located primarily in Greater Copenhagen, Zealand, Bornholm, Fyn, and Jutland. Its property portfolio includes residential, office, retail, hotel, and storage properties. The company was formerly known as Nordicom A/S and changed its name to Park Street Nordicom A/S in June 2017. The company was founded in 1989 and is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark. Park Street Nordicom A/S is a subsidiary of Park Street Asset Management Limited.

VIPRO.CO.summary: Victoria Properties A/S focuses on acquisitions, administration, and operation of commercial and residential properties in Denmark. The company was incorporated in 1941 and is based in Copenhagen, Denmark.
